<seg id=1> China Insurance Supervision Project Starts in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua Press Agency, Beijing, January 21, Telegram:  A research project with the objects of assisting the People's Bank of China in supervising insurance law regulations established for foreign investment insurance agencies in China and exploring insurance standardization systems and measures started recently in Beijing. </seg>
<seg id=3> Financial assistance for this project was provided by the British Royal Sun Joint Insurance Group Company and the U.S. Lincoln Citizen Corporation, and it was specifically underwritten by the U.S. Yongdao Accounting Agency at a total investment of US$ 1.4 million. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> This insurance supervision project will systematically analyze China's foreign investment insurance and current insurance supervision laws and regulations, borrowing from advanced foreign experience to develop a constructive research proposal beneficial to the development of Chinese insurance supervision and to improving the supervision of the legal system and regulations. </seg>
<seg id=5> The insurance supervision project that is being started will conduct a more in-depth study on the basis of the current Foreign Investment Insurance Agency Insurance Supervision Regulations of the People's Bank of China in an effort to strengthen agency organization and conduct procedural management, particularly in developing an early warning system. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Based on what is known, the new supervision rules and regulations will improve the current system of supervising foreign investment insurance agencies in the Chinese market, as well as assist the People's Bank of China in strengthening the current system of overall insurance market supervision. </seg>
</p>
